  "text": "A different pattern of performance was obtained for vowels. Asymptotic performance was obtained with 4 steps in all channel conditions except for n=6. Vowel performance seemed to be more dependent on the number of channels available, which was not surprising since fine spectral resolution is needed for accurate vowel identification. High vowel identification scores (> 90%) were obtained with 8 or more channels, in agreement with our previous findings [CITATION_1] . The vowel performance obtained with 8 or more channels and 4 steps was not significantly different than the vowel performance obtained in the unquantized condition.",
